<h3> References </h3>
<ol>
    <li>G. V. Dunne: <i>Aspects of Chern Simons Theory</i>, Lectures at the 1998 Les Houches Summer School on Topological Aspects of Low Dimensional Systems.<br>
Available at <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/9902115">arXiv:hep-th/9902115</a></li>

    <li>A. M. Tsvelik: <i>Quantum Field Theory in Condensed Matter Physics</i>, Cambridge University Press (2003).</li>

    <li>For more details on Chern-Simons theory as it is discussed by mathematicians, check the <a href="http://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/HomePage">nLab</a> page on <a href="http://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Chern-Simons+theory">Chern-Simons theory</a>.</li>
    
    <li>S. Weinberg: <i>The Quantum Theory of Fields, Vol. 1: Foundations</i>, Cambridge University Press (2005).</li>
    
    <li>L. Susskind: <i>The Quantum Hall Fluid and Non-Commutative Chern-Simons Theory</i>.<br>
Available at <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0101029">arXiv:hep-th/0101029</a></li>
